			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody">I think Turkey would be a reasonable model for introducing democratic institutions. Yep, they need the army to toss out the fundies that get into power from time to time, but, in my opinion, is the most useful model for a mideastern country. Other countries would have to go too far back into history to pull up something useful. It is the most advanced technically and economically. Pretty much all the rest have economies based on oil, and when the oil is gone, they will be gone.
<br />

<br />
Other countries:
<br />
Egypt: too much power in one person. Fundies are screwing it up.
<br />
Iran: we, the USA, overthrew the lawfully elected government of Iran and installed our fine puppet Shah Reza Pahlavi. Now its infested with fundies. What happened in 1979 is a perfect example of what happens when fundies (of any faith) will do when they take over.
<br />
Kuwait: is democratic on paper only, the royal family runs it just like the House of Saud runs Saudi Arabia.
<br />
Saudia Arabia: probably next on the menu for invasion. And it will be soon, they are too busy financially funding fundies, like AlQeda.
<br />

<br />
Most have clan based systems, not a caste system. Big difference.
<br />

<br />
Breaking the country up into 3 pieces would guarantee instant war with Turkey, since Kurdish rebellion has been going on for decades, and a neighboring Kurdistan would make the situation far worse: bad enough to go to war over. A federation will collapse almost immediately. Remember Serbia and Bosnia? Want more? Hassles with Turkey have centered on this issue. A permanent US military presence would be required to protect Kurdistan from Turkish invasion.
<br />

<br />
The biggest disadvantage of using Turkey as model: more kurds have died under Turkey's rule than under sadam's. Kurdush activists claim numbers as high as 14 million killed since the end of WW1. The army has to depose elected governments frequently to keep the country secular. Good example? no, but one that works for the region. 
<br />

<br />
The hardest part of making a peace last in the region will be to set the dial way back on fundies in both the US and Islamic worlds.<span class="gensmall"></span>


