				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody">LOL, Antonelf, you're a funny guy. You try so hard to debate, but always you end up looking like a semi-literate, backwoods Montanan with a stash of grenades and eleven cousins you call your "Freedom Militia". Point to anything in Elberich's post that is anti-US and I'll send you a cookie. If you'd be so kind as to head back to F&R and get owned for everybody's amusement, this has the potential to be one of the more civil threads in the forum. 
<br />

<br />
I kind of agree that a Federation would collapse fairly quickly, simply because three provinces consisting of three different ethnic groups would be at each others' throats sooner or later. The threat to and from surrounding countries would likely never go away. Keeping a multinational military in Iraq wouldn't be feasible in the long run, and even in the short term I think resentment would ensure continued bombings and strife.
<br />

<br />
You're right, though -- a republic may be a bit of a stretch for a people used to being left out of the process of governance. There aren't really a lot of models out there for the situation, and GW is going to have a tough time bringing stability and independence to that country. 
<br />

<br />
In spite of my views, I wish him luck, because the common Iraqi deserves stability.<span class="gensmall"></span>


