				<td colspan="2" align="left"><div class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">In fact, Canada even tried to broker a compromise between the U.S. and the U.N., in an attempt to make everybody come out a winner, a compromise that really only amounted to postponing the whole thing while the inspectors finished up.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Finished up? For what the 5th or 6th round of frustrated and useless inspections?  Allowing Hussein to bide his time was one of the major problems we were facing.  Iraq had been sitting in this negotiated stalemate for 13 or 14 years and had all the opportunity in the world to hide away the WMD programs.
<br />

<br />
The man had holes dug all over Iraq to hide in.  His plan for evasion was so well thought out that he evaded capture for many, many, many months.  How well do you think he could hide chemicals and equpment that doesn't need to eat, drink, or breathe?
<br />

<br />
Items that could be crated up as farming equipment; Buried in caves; Stored in water tanks; Cemented into the foundations of factories; Buried in the massive sand embankments of missle batteries; Or, cached away just about anywhere, undectable and unseen.  How do you get recent intellegence on a few score cubic meters of material when it doesnt need to ever reveal itself? How can you describe what to look for when it  can look just about like anything mundane?
<br />

<br />
We know he had WMD and some of them were tagged by inspectors. There is still massive amounts of mustard gas and nerve agent unaccounted for.  The inspectors couldnt account for it.  Hussein could not account for it.  After months of occupation, the coalition still cant account for it.  It existed; Yet, where did it go?  Why hasn't the stuff we know existed but had not been accounted for been found?
<br />

<br />
Because its searching for a needle in a haystack.  Iraq is a fairly sizable haystack.  How couldyou demand even after a year to have them turn up much less 2 days after bagdad was occupied.  Arguing the WMD is an easy pot shot at the US.  It is pot shot specificly aimed at aiding the enemy.
<br />

<br />
Of all the reasons to go after Iraq the WMD one was harped on by the media and Iraqs secret (perhaps unwitting) allies in the UN.  It was not the one that was most important.  It is the one that Canada and France and Germany made the most important.  We saw it here in our own forums.
<br />

<br />
Americans wanted Hussein gone after 9/11 because he was a vocal and active threat to us and we had been attacked.  Secretly building and hiding WMD was a single item on a long list of specific acts of war.  We went on a wartime footing after 9/11.  We announced it and asked our allies for support.
<br />

<br />
Hussein was on the short list.  Our intention to go there after Afghanistan was done was all but shouted over loud speakers.  We were already in a massive policing action.  They guy had threatened us with terrorism.  He trained terrorists.  He was going down.
<br />

<br />
After 13+ years, are you telling me that Canada wanted to negotiate the stalemate to take just a little longer?  And, I should take this as a show of alliance?
<br />

<br />
I see it as buying Hussein more time.
<br />

<br />
His hiding out in Iraq is evidence that his plan was to remain until international pressure got the coalition out of his way to return.  Everyone in Iraq knew his plan.  That is what kept the marginal ones talking @#%$ on TV and the crazy ones blowing themselves up on roadblocks.
<br />

<br />
That pressure, mirrorred here, and at US embassies and in your press (and ours in the US <img src="images/smiles/frown.gif" alt="frown" border="0" /> ), was a weapon for Hussein and against the US.
<br />

<br />
If I seem black and white to you.  I question if you understand the gravity of the evennts on 9/11.  That was a left over affect of our contention with the soviets to keep them from occupying our allies.  Now, our homeland and civilians have been attacked brutally and our once allies are actively frustrating our defense.
<br />

<br />
I can see all sorts of shades of gray my friend; But, this is off the chart.  Arguing against removing Hussein in the light of 9/11 is like arguing against the eradication of small pox as an epidemic is raging.  Hussein is not the end either.  There are still several other countries that have been called to the mat and if they don't make quick with the happy happy peace peace talk we will see more war.
<br />

<br />
I expect our allies to get in line.  Negotiations are good.  But, when attacked, the sort of behavior I rightfully expect from my allies is standing shoulder to shoulder with me, not taking book on how long till I get knocked down.
<br />

<br />
The position Canada has taken with Iraq, regardless of intention, has been detrimental.  The positions taken taken by France and Germany almost unforgivable.  Russia, never pretended to be our friend, they are pushing being viewed as an enemy again.
<br />

<br />
The US is not going to be attacked and not directly intervene against its enemies.
<br />

<br />
###
<br />

<br />
Here's an analogy for those challenged in the honor category:
<br />

<br />
You are sitting in a club with a couple friends.  Suddenly a bottle hits you in the back of your head.  This is not the first bottle that came whizzing your way. It is the first one that connected.
<br />

<br />
In the club are a couple street punks that have been threatening you and a few others in the neighborhood. They believe that "Your kind don't belong here." and they express it in violent destructive ways.
<br />

<br />
They guffaw at the look of shock on your face. One does a little dance. Another pantomimes your bottle driven head snap in slow motion.  Another with his hands behind his back says, "I aint got no bottles and I didnt do it. But, you got it comin and more (clink)." Yet another says "I been drinking that beer with the Heavy %@$# bottles just for you. How do you like me now?"
<br />

<br />
With the ability to obliterate all of them 10 times over. What do you do?
<br />
Chasing one out of the club, and putting the smart %@$# with his hands behind his back in a choke hold seems like damn appropriate response.  Now, that guy who said he had extra heavy bottles, I wonder if he'd like to discuss the fine art of glass blowing in more constructive ways...
<br />

<br />
If your friends are really your friends, what do they do?
<br />

<br />
As it turns out, your "friends" were buying dope from the punks. Well France, and Germany were, Canada was just getting smoked out for free. When the bottle hit they gasped.  They were still in shock when you chased the one dude out.  When you took the guy on with his hands was holding something behind his back, they recoiled.  "No, stop, not the dope man!" they cried.
<br />

<br />
What they really didnt want you to find out was that what he had behind his back was the checks they wrote for dope. Canada had been selling to you significantly higher.  This was after you all agreed that you wouldnt get dope from from those thugs when you found out they kicked that little Kuwaiti kids face in.
<br />

<br />
Well, the dope man is down.  Even that awkward new Polish kid stood up for right.  Canada says he never bought from the dude.  But he sure didnt want you finding out the streetmarket value or taking out a possible future connection.
<br />

<br />
Man, you have known Canada since you were both in diapers too. You've not known him to get in too many fights. But, to go up and start snatching on your arm while you are actively defending yourself against thugs?
<br />

<br />
Something is up with that.<span class="gensmall"></span>


